T 766 (Location of corresponding print.) (corresponding photographic print) LOT 2315 (Location of corresponding print.) (corresponding photographic print)", "site": ["pictures", "catalog"], "subject": ["york", "pennsylvania", "york county", "safety film negatives", "united states"], "timestamp": "2022-04-26T09:25:08.662Z", "title": "York, Pennsylvania. Pennsylvania-Dutch farm", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2017859697/"}], "resource": {"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/scu/batch_scu_dogwood_ver01/data/sn84026925/0029586283A/1921021801/0112.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:scu:batch_scu_dogwood_ver01:data:sn84026925:0029586283A:1921021801:0105/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/scu/batch_scu_dogwood_ver01/data/sn84026925/0029586283A/1921021801/0112.pdf", "segment_count": 8, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84026925/1921-02-18/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}, "resources": [{"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/scu/batch_scu_dogwood_ver01/data/sn84026925/0029586283A/1921021801/0112.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:scu:batch_scu_dogwood_ver01:data:sn84026925:0029586283A:1921021801:0105/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/scu/batch_scu_dogwood_ver01/data/sn84026925/0029586283A/1921021801/0112.pdf", "segment_count": 8, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84026925/1921-02-18/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/scu/batch_scu_dogwood_ver01/data/sn84026925/0029586283A/1921021801/0112.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84026925/1921-02-18/ed-1/?sp=8"], "batch": ["scu_dogwood_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/south carolina/", "2/united states/south carolina/york/", "3/united states/south carolina/york/york/"], "contributor": ["university of south carolina; columbia, sc"], "date": "1921-02-18", "dates": ["1921-02-18"], "description": ["Itumorous department Well PreservedFormer Senator John Weeks of Massachusetts has long enjoyed an established reputation as a naval expert but only lately has he blossomed out as an Orientalist A few days ago at a public gathering he made formal announce Inent of a highly important discovery of a collection of Babylonian tablets covered with coneiform inscriptions Mr Weeks said that the importance of these tablets was entirely due to ihoiv snhiert matter As a rule Chaldean tablets bear records of laws commercial transactions and royal decrees but those to which the speaker referred preserved for a remote posterity specimens of eastmen humor that were hoary with ape when Babylon was a village One ct these tablets according to Mr Weeks chronicled a royal ball that the king gave in honor of one of Methuselahs birthdays when that notoriously aged person was pretty well along in years It appeared that one of the ladies of the court having paid her respects to the guest of honor made bold to ask him which birthday he was celebrating I am nine hundred and sixty years old today my dear replied the ancient You dont say so replied the lady in her best"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2024-01-24T14:39:05.361Z", "group": ["ndnp/scu", "university-of-south-carolina-columbia-sc-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84026925/1921-02-18/ed-1/?sp=8", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:scu:batch_scu_dogwood_ver01:data:sn84026925:0029586283A:1921021801:0112/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg#h=279&w=201", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-service